		 <h1 class="one">The Little War (La Guerra Chiquita)</h1> 
		<p><br>Cuba's second rebellion against Spanish rule was organized in New
		  York by veterans of the <em>Ten Year War</em> lead by <em>Calixto
		  Garc&iacute;a</em> (pictured), one of the few revolutionary leaders who did not
		  sign the <em>Pact of Zanj&oacute;n</em> (see Ten Year War), and Jos&eacute;
		  Maceo (brother of Antonio), Guillermo Moncada, Emilo N&uacute;&ntilde;ez and
		  others. </p> 
		<p>In 1878 Garc&iacute;a issued a manifesto against Spanish despotism and
		  <em>La Guerra Chiquita</em> (The Little War) started officially in Cuba on
		  August 26 1879. After a few brief victories the war ended by September 1880 in
		  rebel defeat. </p> 
        <p><strong>Related</strong>:<br>The <a href="tenyear.htm">Ten Year War</a> | The <a href="../scaw/spawar.htm">War for Independence</a><br></p>
		 
			 
	     
  
 
